    "body": "Once https://github.com/rapidsai/cudf/issues/15612 is implemented, libcudf can make further use of the pool to optimize data transfers.\r\n\r\nTypes like `device_scalar` can use a small pinned buffer, since pool makes the allocation cost rivial. Also, use of `std::vector`s as the host mirror of device data (e.g. `make_device_uvector_async`, `make_std_vector_async`) can be replaced with a type backed with pinned memory, at least for buffers that are not in the same order of magnitude with the data size.",
